{"lemma":"إِسْكاف","slug":"إِسْكاف","root":"س.ك.ف","root_slug":"س-ك-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20247"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A5%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%81"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shoemaker, cobbler"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Classical Syriac ܐܶܫܟܳܦܳܐ (ʾeškāp̄ā, “shoemaker”), from Akkadian 𒀿 (AŠGAB /⁠aškāpu⁠/)."},"ipa":["/ʔis.kaːf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20247","headword_ar":"اـِسْكَافٌ","root":"skf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, S, M, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usokuwfN","text_ar":"اُسْكُوفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asokafN","text_ar":"اَسْكَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sak~aAfN","text_ar":"سَكَّافٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayokafN","text_ar":"سَيْكَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A maker of boots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of shoes"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sandals;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sewer of boots"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (Msb;) or the first word, (Msb, K, TA,) as used by the Arabs [of the desert], (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any artificer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"artisan,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA,) thus expl. in the M, and so its three [perhaps a mistake for four] dial. vars., but said by J [in the S] to be a meaning not known, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except the maker of boots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for he is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asokafN","text_ar":"اَسْكَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) i. e. when they mean such as is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isokaAfN","text_ar":"اـِسْكَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the cities or towns or villages: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a carpenter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) in which sense it is used by Esh-Shemmákh, but J says, [in the S,] only on the ground of supposition; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any handicraftsman who works with an iron tool:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K, * TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAkifapN","text_ar":"اَسَاكِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAkiyfu","text_ar":"اَسَاكِيفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-  Also the first word,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Skilful"},{"kind":"text","text":"with an affair. (O, K.) Sh says, I heard El-Fak'asee say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aka lA_isokaAfN bih`*aA AlA^amori","text_ar":"اـِنَّكَ لاـِسْكَافٌ بِهٰذَا الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily thou art skilful with this affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.)       -A2-  Accord. to Ibn-'Abbád,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isokaAfu","text_ar":"الاـِسْكَافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used (O, K) by Ibn-Mukbil (O) as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The redness of wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is a mistranscription, (O, K,) and a perversion of the meaning: (O:) the right word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isokaAb","text_ar":"الاـِسْكَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Sh","S","M","K","Msb","TA","O"]}]}}